column1: Who will win the 2017 Academy Award for Actress in a Supporting Role?
column5: ['Viola Davis (Fences)', 'Naomie Harris (Moonlight)', 'Nicole Kidman (Lion)', 'Octavia Spencer (Hidden Figures)', 'Michelle Williams (Manchester by the Sea)']
column11: The 89th Academy Awards® take place on Sunday, February 26. Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

column6: She just won the Harvard Foundation's Artist of the Year... more credible recognition from critics and professionals. Adjust up 1%
Adjust up from 87%--> 93% for Viola Davis b/c she won a BAFTA. She cleared all major pre-Oscar awards (BAFTA, CC, GG, and SAG), making it even more probable she will win the Oscar.

No one holds a candle to Viola Davis this year in her role in Fences. Even just from the commercials, I got shivers. She won the Golden Globe for her role, and I see no reason to believe that she wouldn't continue on to win the Oscar.
